cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the coexistence and interference between two heterogeneous systems, namely an air traffic control radar and a wide area cellular communication system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design, implementation, and analysis of communication networks. The paper also involves the analysis of interference and signal processing, which falls under the categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the security and reliability of the radar system, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
